</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">Public
Policy and its amendment to better the face of the planet has always
been the sole driving force for me. I have worked on several small
and big problems alike and tried to the best of my efforts and
knowledge to bring it to a better shape. The MPP program shall
develop me as an individual equipped with tools to efficiently and
skilfully apply my knowledge to find solutions which are for the
public good. </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">There
have been some very particular experiences which have triggered this
thought.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">It
was the time when I was working with the Government of India\'s
project named \'Clean India Movement\' or the Swachh Bharat Abhiyan as
it is popularly known as. Under the scheme, I was heading the team
which was designated with the responsibility of motivating people to
construct toilets/latrines in their homes. India has long faced this
criticism and it has quite a lot maligned the country\'s image when it
comes to hygiene. The people are not willing to construct a toilet
inside the premises of their homes because of various cultural and
religious issues with absolutely no solid premise. Because of this,
over 40% of the rape cases that happen in rural areas are because of
the reason that women go out alone in the dark for the natural call. </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">So,
when we were out in the field and I was given the charge of two of
the most adamant cities, Hapur and Ghaziabad which have a long
history of not complying with authorities.  </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">When
our team approached the individual houses, we were greeted with
straight faces and threats to life. I knew that putting force and
making the reluctant people do something by subjugation wouldn\'t
solve the problem, so I introduced a moral tactic. With the help of
local authorities, I identified a woman in each village who had
undergone molestation or rape (due to not having toilets in homes)
and was courageous enough to lodge a public complaint. I made them
the leaders of the individual teams and let them lead the small units
to approach the other women in other houses. I knew that a woman to
woman talk would be much more effective and that too when coming from
a victim of such an event the primary cause of which was the absence
of toilets in homes. Also, it was the woman in the house who had the
highest capability to persuade the men of the house to make the
construction of the toilet possible. We made sure that each household
that agreed to construct one got a handsome compensation to do so
from the government. Not to our surprise, we registered 4400 requests
for toilet construction within 4 months of hard work. I don\'t just
consider it my individual achievement, but the achievement of the
entire unit working with us who actually realised my idea and backed
my leadership.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">This
experience taught me how to bring change on the ground as an
individual and with a small team, but to make this change
sustainable, a good academic backing is as necessary as it seems. As
of now, there is one project that I am working on and looking forward
to proliferate its impact all across the nation. This particular
project is what prompted me to go for a Public Policy degree at the
masters level.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">As
India nears universal enrolment, there is a growing realization that
bringing children into schools doesn’t equate to quality learning.
In fact, as the conversation has moved away from enrolment, there is
an active shift towards seeking factors that deliver and influence
access and quality. There are more than 1 million public schools in
India. But numerous problems like poor school infrastructure and
learning environment, lack of adequately trained teachers, high
teacher absenteeism, no internet or technology use, and lack of
accessibility to name a few, contribute to a staggering dropout rate
that sees nearly 50% of children abandoning their education at the
key transitional ages of school. Well, for me to start with, tackling
all of these problems together would be equivalent to trying to push
a wall. Hence, my motivation is towards solving one, ‘quality of
content delivery and ensuring accessibility’. </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">It
is the proliferation of experiential context-based learning (which we
are making completely digital) that is missing. And poor students
have no idea about what they are being deprived of. If not for the
\'community schools\', the children will be forced into hazardous job
sectors such as firecracker industries, rag-picking and prostitution.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">Now
for the implementation part, I have started working with the
‘community schools’ first because it is the only entity with no
set curriculum or teachers per-se and most of them are situated in
remote at-risk areas. There are more than 400,000 major community
schools in India and almost one in each village/town. We are adopting
such schools one by one and delivering our content, which requires
absolutely no teacher facilitation and is made interesting enough
using graphics and animations in 12 regional languages and seven
different subjects (which our partners and mentors are curating), to
change lives and improve student retention rates.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">After
the successful MVP of the project, I am going forward with national
level policy recommendations to the government and looking forward to
transform how education is delivered at the very primary level.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.17in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">In
the year 2018, I also took to the technology side of things to
support Both education, and accessibility in the most rural parts of
India. I was selected from amongst the thousands to be able to
represent my country at the prestigious Youth@</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #000000">IGF</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">
program by the Internet Society in Paris and </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #000000">ICANN64</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">
Meeting by the International Corporation for assigned names and
numbers at Kobe, Japan. At both the fellowships, I have been striving
hard to promote policies of better accessibility and a more open and
free internet for the remotest parts of India where we are trying to
establish online based ‘teacher-less’ learning pedagogy using the
digital content and online facilitation developed at our organisation
wit the help of world-class teachers and mentors from the field. We
already successfully implemented the initiative at several places and
are looking forward to the Internet Society to push our
recommendations forward to the respective stakeholders who may
support us in ways more than one. By far, the results have been
positive and we are going to organise a regional meeting of the
Internet Governance Forum very soon in India to take the efforts
forward.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">Last
but not the least, why I chose HKUST as a study centre is because of
the fact that both India and </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #000000">China</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">
are the future leaders of the world. What we do here, will be
followed by the rest. And it is in these two nations that a large
level of social intervention is required because of the sheer
population and diversity so as to secure a sustainable future. Hence
getting the Asian understanding of the domain and gaining expert
knowledge from a pool of experts amalgamating technology, public
policy, environment and sustainability is a mix which is found in no
other Asian University. Hong kong respects the academic integrity and
freedom of both the teachers and the students and that is what gives
so much scope to the country and the people living there and places
HKUST as the top choice for someone like me.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<DIV TYPE=FOOTER>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-top: 0.16in; margin-bottom: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none">
<BR>
</P>
</DIV>
</BODY>
</HTML>',
