<BODY LANG="en-US" DIR="LTR">
<DIV TYPE=HEADER>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.26in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none">
<BR>
</P>
</DIV>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><SUB><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><B><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">International
summer school on sustainable tourism- Iran</SPAN></B></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR>
</P>
<OL>
<LI><P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">Relevant
experiences: Having been to over 30 countries and over 100 cities
abroad, I have seen the best practices all around the world. Coming
from India, tourism and sustainability were never complimentary
concepts in theory or practical. Nor did it cross my own mind till I
started working on a research project to study negative effects of
tourism and increased footfalls in the ancient area of Chandni
Chowk, in the region of Old </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #000000">Delhi
</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">which
happens to be the capital territory of India. While surveying we
found astonishing results and proposed the government to provide us
with a research grant to further our studies on the topic. After one
year of intensive research I published a research paper which dealt
with devising a “tourist management street path venturing” which
talked about designing a sustainable path with strategies to deal
with the excessive influx of footfalls in the old market area.
Taking that study as a basis, The Government of Thailand in
collaboration with  10th International Convention of Asia Scholars
invited me as a guest speaker to present my study and be on the
panel of Sustainable tourism along with other experts and later
published my study titled, “Tourism as a medium to achieve
socio-cultural sustainability in South Asia”. </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>
</P>
</OL>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">Later
next year, I went on to work with the Mayor of Venice, Italy and took
part in the ‘Study Days’ organised at the International Study and
Documentation Centre for Youth by the University of Trieste. Here, we
chalked out a plan to sustainably manage tourists and reduce carbon
emissions along with preserving the heritage of Venice. The Mayor
readily accepted the proposal and the study was published in the iSDC
conference journal.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">It
was here in Italy that I met an associate researcher working under
the Office of the President of Ukraine and she asked of me to submit
a proposal on ‘Sustainable development of territories’ which
happened to be the general theme of the ‘VII International
Scientific Conference’ organised by the &quot;Dnipropetrovsk
Regional Institute of Public Administration of the National Academy
for public Administration under the President of Ukraine”. The
proposal that I submitted won a special certificate of Appreciation
and got a place in the yearly issue of the conference and got taken
into consideration to be enacted upon by the Public Policy Institute
which was a huge achievement for me as a ‘Sustainable tourism’
proponent and enthusiast. Currently, I am working on a comparative
study of sustainable tourism planning in </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #000000">China</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">
and India with a special focus on the city of the future- Shenzhen
(</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #000000">China</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">)
where I am currently residing.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">2.
Iran being one of those countries I have always dreamt of visiting,
both because it has been the centre of culture and heritage. The
interest started to develop when we  first got to know about the
history and culture of Iran by one of our Professors at the
</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #000000">University
of Delhi</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">
who had studied the Persian Language and cultural studies in Iran and
was a close associate of the Cultural centre of Iran at the Iranian
embassy in </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #000000">New
Delhi</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">.
Then, everything struck back last year, when I was selected for a
trekking journey sponsored by the United Nations all along the
deserts of Oman starting from Yemen all the way to Iran. On the way,
I was accompanied by 19 different people from as many nationalities
and our task was to discuss and devise strategies to lift the veil up
from the stereotypes of the Middle Eastern countries and promote
sustainable tourism along with projecting Islamic history to the
world. That was a wonderful experience and a fruitful one indeed,
after which I thought Iran also needs something like this for the
rest of the world to understand this nation better. If I get selected
to participate in this summer school, I shall absorb in as much
positives and would strive my best to publish a research taking in
the best practices of sustainable tourism from Iran whilst promoting
the rich cultural and historical richness of the land. Persian
culture offers us another picture on the big canvas of the general
Islamic culture and makes the world understand that the world is not
the same everywhere. Also, I really want to bring in my knowledge and
experience on the table when we discuss issues of utmost importance
to better the tourist inflows and sustainably manage them for Iran
and would like to see my practical experience being used for
something amazing in the land.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<DIV TYPE=FOOTER>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-top: 0.16in; margin-bottom: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none">
<BR>
</P>
</DIV>
</BODY>
</HTML>',
