<DIV TYPE=HEADER>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.96in"><BR>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><B>Describe a past or current project
or work you are/were involved in and how this was successful in
creating change?</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in">I co-founded an organization, The
<SPAN STYLE="background: #000000">Maslow Initiative Foundation</SPAN>.
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT COLOR="#333333"><FONT FACE="Roboto, serif"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">The
organisation that I founded i.e. ‘</SPAN></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#333333"><FONT FACE="Roboto, serif"><SPAN STYLE="background: #000000">Maslow
Initiative Foundation’</SPAN></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#333333"><FONT FACE="Roboto, serif"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">
works with community schools across India. And we call the project
‘Abrazos’ which means embracing. As the name goes, we literally
adopt and embrace these schools and implement our innovative learning
methodology. I believe and I am, a strong advocate of value-based
experiential learning rather than theoretical bookish knowledge
dissemination. India, the land of ‘vedas’, proudly owning
millions of books and artifacts which deliver knowledge in a
purposeful and practical way. The lessons, be it of science,
mathematics or humanities, were all taught using storytelling and
pictures. </SPAN></FONT></FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT COLOR="#333333"><FONT FACE="Roboto, serif"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">Now
what we are doing is, taking the best out of these texts and making
our own digital knowledge dissemination coursework for community
schools. I have partnered with leading content producer Mr. Arvind
Gupta (awarded Padma Shree, one of India’s highest civilian
honours) and now we have a digital repository of over a thousand
books for children of all ages in more than 10 languages! Each of
this book/resource contains graphically designed content for subjects
like mathematics, moral science, Hindi, science, history, politics,
that is commendably designed for a total practical learning
experience.</SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT COLOR="#333333"><FONT FACE="Roboto, serif"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">Now
for the implementation part, I have started working with the
‘community schools’ first because it is the only entity with no
set curriculum or teachers per say. There are more than 400,000 major
community schools in India,  and almost one in each village/town. We
are adopting such schools one by one and delivering our content to
change lives and improve student retention rates which happens to be
less than 10%. </SPAN></FONT></FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT COLOR="#333333"><FONT FACE="Roboto, serif"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">In
the 10+ schools that we have already adopted, we showcase this
digital content using projectors. Projector as a medium because,
first, they are cheaper than computers or tablets (&lt;USD 12);
second, can cater to a larger audience at once. Then comes the
content transportation, which we do using flash drives, which is the
cheapest method to do so.</SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT COLOR="#333333"><FONT FACE="Roboto, serif"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">As
far as sustainability of this project is concerned, we use a very
unique ‘village-financing model’. What we do is that, motivate
each villager to contribute a one time cost of INR 01 which equals to
less than 1/65 of a US dollar. In India, each village easily has a
population of over 1000 dwellers, hence we have the required amount
generated for the projector. Now to return the favour, we screen one
bollywood movie (with a moral message) each Sunday for the villagers
in the school’s premises or a community place, free of cost. This
way, people never hesitate to even contribute more than what we ask,
happily, as they get good dose of entertainment and learnings for
themselves. As it is a win-win situation for all, we have 100%
cooperation rate from the village/town authorities as well and till
now have managed to deliver 800 digital books across these villages.</SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><B>What is your motivation for
participating in this event?</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in">The sensitisation regarding certain
specific access and quality related issues about education is one of
the most fundamental brain shift that I want to bring about. Event
like this would help changemakers like me to proliferate our region’s
realities and make them the world’s. The ever increasing gap
between our young population and quality education is what motivates
me to delve into the facet of deep moral enquiry and ground work to
see a better world for our little brothers and sisters.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; line-height: 100%">
As India nears universal enrolment, there is a growing realization
that bringing children into schools doesn’t equate to quality
learning. In fact, as the conversation has moved away from enrolment,
there is an active shift towards seeking factors that deliver and
influence quality. There are more than 1 million public schools in
India. But numerous problems like poor school infrastructure and
learning environment, lack of adequately trained teachers, high
teacher absenteeism, a large volume of teacher vacancies, low levels
of learning and achievement and lack of accountability to name a few
contribute to a staggering dropout rate that sees nearly 50% children
abandoning their education at the key transitional ages of school.
Well, for me to start with, tackling all of these problems together
would be equivalent to trying to push a wall. Hence, my motivation is
towards solving one, ‘the quality of content delivery and
facilitation’.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; line-height: 100%">
Knowledge nowadays is merely theoretical, taught like a formality,
with no applications. The purpose of knowledge accumulated throughout
thousands of years, we have forgotten. The method of imparting
knowledge has not changed, despite the vast syllabi, our system
continues to hold onto the orthodox methodology. Some children, if
not all, do not find anything enthusiastic, yet they continue to
churn the words to make sense and fail miserably.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; line-height: 100%">
The education system has a grip on the children, relieving them of
their freedom. It is slow, yes, but steady. The system focuses more
on the children to become followers of the system rather than leaders
and hence the disinterest and amplification in drop-out rates.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; line-height: 100%">
Before the introduction of a proper, formal system of education,
knowledge was preserved in the form of stories and skills, arts and
crafts, imitation and application. This knowledge was passed down to
the generations, each generation adding their own to the already
existing skill, perfecting it, and honing it, one at a time. It is
this experiential context-based learning that is missing. And poor
students have no idea about what they are being deprived of.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; line-height: 100%">
This even shall give my voice a stage and my work a credibility, the
steps of which my fellows could follow and bring a revolution in the
education system and help advance SDG 4. 
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; line-height: 100%">
<BR><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><B>If selected, how will you use your
attendance at the WORLD MEET Summit 2018 to advance your community
work and/or goals?</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; line-height: 100%">
Meeting and interacting with such people who share a common humanity
and believe in themselves as global citizens are the best fellow
audience one can get to proliferate the workable ideas for the
benefit of the entire \'overlooked community\'(here: children). I
believe that the problems are the same everywhere, it is just the
scale and complexity of it which might make it different in different
societies and countries per say. And if we think globally about it
and further the action by acting locally for our own communities,
this lot of changemakers coming at the WYF can make the real
difference.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; line-height: 100%">
<BR><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; line-height: 100%">
Reaching out to like-minded people to broaden the understanding of
the ground issue that I am working on, to be able to gather unique
and impacting ideas that may be taken as best practice examples and
hence be replicated in my settings. The people coming from diverse
backgrounds and disciplines shall help leverage the expertise of
their particular domains and we can all brainstorm possible newer
solutions in addition to our existing approaches of bringing about
change in our societies. To further the goals of my project, it will
be multiple folds beneficial to have partnerships and volunteers to
be able to convert it into a huge success whilst impacting so many
direct beneficiaries who shall be the backbone of the world tomorrow.
My project as of now needs a good volunteer base who shall act as
facilitators form a different culture. Through this, even the
volunteers will have a once in a lifetime experience of living for
free in a local village and having the unique teaching experience
with equally unique pedagogy. Then the access to our partner
organisations attending the summit will be an asset for our project
as we can have possibly great content and delivery, digital,
technological and other partners coming from all over the world. 
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; line-height: 100%">
Then the access to the summit\'s network is the greatest advantage
subjected to us by all means. The long-term association and
interaction with fellows and mentors will pave a way for us which
shall exponentially increase our impact multiple folds. I want the
issue we are working on as part of the SDG proliferation campaign to
gain a global limelight and what better place to have this kind of
global presence than World Youth Forum.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; line-height: 100%">
<BR><BR>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
</BODY>
