<span id="_14.8" style=" font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14.8px; color:#000000">
stories are being then viewed by a gendered perspective. The three mirrors of gender, narratives and </span>
</div>
<div class="pos" id="_103:642" style="top:642;left:103">
<span id="_14.8" style=" font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14.8px; color:#000000">
China tend to create a kaleidoscopic image such that will be interesting to see the patterns evolving out.</span>
</div>
<div class="pos" id="_78:660" style="top:660;left:78">
<span id="_14.8" style=" font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:14.8px; color:#000000">
4. Both India and China share a history where one gender has always been seen with the eye of subjugation </span>
</div>
