in his famous book \'The Republic\' gives us an example of a sweet shop
owner and a doctor being contestants for an election. The former
while giving his election debate brags about how he will make all the
sweets free to eat and no restriction on anybody to eat as much. Then
Plato asks, what should the Doctor say? If he says I do what I do for
the benefit of the people, I open skulls, cause you trouble, just to
make you better- wouldn\'t sound great for an election speech, right?
And ultimately the sweet seller wins. This is what is happening in
our modern day politics as well. We want more doctors and not sweet
sellers to actually benefit the society. </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">GYS
will give me the skills to become a doctor, a public policy
enthusiast already, I need to hone my skills and sharpen my prowess
to command a great change in our education system. Secondly, I have
already embarked on the vision of \'educating all\' and I tend to do
this in an innovative way.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
