Germany and </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #000000">Sinal
do Vale</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Helvetica Neue, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">,
Brazil as our mentors and patrons. I will proliferate the learnings
at GYS and deploy those skills and expertise to benefit thousands of
people associated with my work back at home here. The most important
asset for me will be the network of changemakers that this summit
provides and the word of mouth support that it shall garner for a
project such as ours. My aim is to amalgamate the support of
international organisations for my organisation and the gathering of
like-minded people at GYS shall ensure that as well. We hope that our
own government also notices our work after we become a part of the
