</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#2d1530"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><B><SPAN STYLE="background: #f7f5f5">How
do you think EF can help you? Please explain</SPAN></B></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#db2a3a"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #f7f5f5">&nbsp;*</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#2d1530"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Arimo, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff"><BR></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#2d1530"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><I><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #f7f5f5">Individuals
apply to EF at different stages of their founding journey, help us to
understand what type of support you are most interested in from EF.</SPAN></SPAN></I></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#2d1530"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #f7f5f5">The
sheer network of mentors and resources that EF has make it one of the
top programs of its kind to go for. I have experienced various ups
and downs and have readily accepted failures as have enjoyed
successes. I believe myself to be a very pragmatic problem solver
upto the extent that I have experienced something similar before. But
life is not always about that. As an entrepreneur, one always comes
across difficult and novel life situations and this is where EF comes
into picture. The cohort spent at EF shall train my mind to accept
and devise solutions while being a part of the family, that’s your
team. Then, after we move on from the cohort, the mere connectedness
to the network bears fruits in ways more than one. Having such a
credible organisation such as EF, shall always go a long way in
building trust amongst my future partners and investors given the
fact of the standard of alma matar I represent.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 107%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#2d1530"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><B><SPAN STYLE="background: #f7f5f5">What
random but surprisingly useful or interesting thing should we know
about you?</SPAN></B></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">My
journey started in much of the veiled circumstances where the
culture, family and society played an important role in the making of
what I am today. Up until the high school the premise of what I knew
was what I had observed which seems to be but-natural. Although the
experience became alleviating when the veil of ignorance was lifted
and the cacophony of the outside world was heard. This was the time
when I moved out to the University for my bachelors and seemed like I
was all on my own. The faint yet omnipresent words of my father still
echo like a thunderous wobbling storm shaking me up when I remember
that “now, you have to make it on your own son”. Although very
rare in our societies yet naturally imposed on many- this situation
is what made me start my own company at the age of 17. I always
wanted to do computer science, but my business acumen won over it and
pulled me towards a school which seemed like was made just right for
me. I gathered a few other enthusiasts of IT and started an IT
service provider company. To make the ground even was not easy
nevertheless the shovel, hoe and sickle were never kept aside. Right
from renting out a small 10X10 room and making it break even within
first month, to hiring 20 employees in the second year- all shall be
attributed to the sheer passion and determination to stand out and on
my own. I wanted to be different, different to and for the world, the
services that we provided were primarily for the social startups and
NGOs who I think should have a greater and prolonged presence online,
but financial constraints never let them achieve so. The strategy was
to take up 60 percent of such work at one third of the market price
and barge in the big corporate clients into our offices for the other
40. That worked and the ice broke, the bearer brightened the light of
the torch and the like-minded followed. </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">It
was the year 2017 when the idea of food wastage tempted me to do
something about it. It was the year I was working with the WWF doing
a voluntary job and a lecture there change my perspective for good. I
put up my savings and started a ethical-green restaurant, the
features of which were no-food wastage as we partnered with various
shelter homes giving them all the stock at the end of the day. No use
of fertilizer produced veggies or chemical induced meat. And the jobs
were first and foremost reserved for the internally migrated laborers
who happened to bring in great finger licking delights from their
regions and presented a plethora of amalgamated cuisines for offer to
our customers. </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">It
went well for more than a year, until recently when financial crisis
struck most of the regions in Pakistan and the prices of the most
basic of goods surged to an unexpected rise. We couldn’t afford
doing the good stuff and with nominal savings, unfortunately, the
place had to shut down. But while even doing so, I made sure that all
of our workers got placed in some other ethical job and could support
their families back home. </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 100%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#000000"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #ffffff">Having
experienced various ups and downs, I feel like just having the
business acumen is not enough, honing it is what matters more. My
initial startup has become self-sustaining and now I can focus on the
more important problems that I want to solve. </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; line-height: 107%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; text-decoration: none; page-break-after: auto">
<BR><BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.11in; background: #ffffff; border: none; padding: 0in; line-height: 107%; page-break-inside: auto; widows: 2; orphans: 2; page-break-after: auto">
<SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#2d1530"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><B><SPAN STYLE="background: #f7f5f5">Who
is the most impressive person you know who should apply? Please
include their LinkedIn or Academic site here</SPAN></B></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-variant: normal"><FONT COLOR="#db2a3a"><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration: none"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal"><SPAN STYLE="background: #f7f5f5">&nbsp;*</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
